		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">pragma wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"> <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />  <em>That darn lockout chip is another issue completely...</em></div>
<br />
<br />Yeah, that is kind of sucky. What I did to my frontloaders is I just took this little scratcher/poker thing that came with my soldering iron, and I just pulled pin 4 right out of the chip itself. I didn't just bend the pin up out of the board, I pulled the pin out of the chip. I don't know too much about legalty of NESdev in general, or about the legalty of the redesigned famicom, but I totally own a Yobo FC console that my brother bought for me, and I'll be using this for dev testing, because it's lockout free. I think, at least. Their real cheap to buy, only $30 dollars for mine. They also work VERY well. Not compatible with CV3 at all. Weird graphical glitches.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
