		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It would be great to have get some new cases.  Isn't the expensive part of injection molding having the actual mold made?  And of course that you'd need to have a lot of cases made with it to make up for whatever other fixed costs there are.
<br />
<br />For lockout chips, we could have a seperate connector for it on the cart maybe.  Could even be detachable.  On the next board I prototype I'm gonna try using the gloptop CICs from Mario/Duckhunt through it's edge connector.  It's just 6 pins.

		

