<br />
<br />I'm sure it's all fair.  As long as it's a replacement rather than an exact copy (the latter would be pretty much impossible anyways).
<br />
<br />A logic analyzer won't do much for us, all the good stuff is inside the chip.  I've got pics of the ROM inside the chip (thanks to neviksti), but I don't know how the memory is organized or what the CPU core is exactly (other than it's 4-bit and possibly by Sharp).  I'm pretty sure I could make a replacement if I could disassemble that.

		

		</td>
