<br />
<br />Yep.  Airborne fiberglass particles, sounds real healthy!  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" /> 
<br />Sawing the PCB apart sounds pretty dirty, but it'd be something.
<br />
<br />It'd be the same style for the detachable version.  The boards would connect with a 6-pin dual-row header.  If it needed to be detachable, the NES board side of it could probably use a female connector.  But then the case needs to be opened to detach it, so I guess that would make sense if I can find some regular screws to replace the security screws.

		

